<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="65" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1527,1984]" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1599,1624]" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Frons brown as 
<figureCitation box="[614,682,1599,1624]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[271,1255,201,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[225,1277,186,1925]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Megaselia anniduedahlae sp. n. male (Figs 1-10). 1. Frons. 2. Postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 3, proboscis from below. 4, left face of hypopygium. 5. Right face of hypopygium. 6. Front leg. 7. segments 4 and 5 of front tarsus. 8. mid tibia. 9. Hind femur. 10. Wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617695/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, with dense but very fine microtrichia. Cheek with 4 bristles and jowl with 1 that is longer. Postpedicels, which lack SPS vesicles, palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation box="[1179,1250,1635,1660]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[271,1255,201,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[225,1277,186,1925]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Megaselia anniduedahlae sp. n. male (Figs 1-10). 1. Frons. 2. Postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 3, proboscis from below. 4, left face of hypopygium. 5. Right face of hypopygium. 6. Front leg. 7. segments 4 and 5 of front tarsus. 8. mid tibia. 9. Hind femur. 10. Wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617695/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
. Proboscis from below as 
<figureCitation box="[269,330,1671,1696]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[271,1255,201,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[225,1277,186,1925]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Megaselia anniduedahlae sp. n. male (Figs 1-10). 1. Frons. 2. Postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 3, proboscis from below. 4, left face of hypopygium. 5. Right face of hypopygium. 6. Front leg. 7. segments 4 and 5 of front tarsus. 8. mid tibia. 9. Hind femur. 10. Wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617695/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Fig.3</figureCitation>
. Thorax brown. Three notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these. Mesopleuron bare. Scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdominal tergites brown with numerous hairs that are longest at rear of T6 (
<figureCitation box="[695,768,1743,1768]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[271,1255,201,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[225,1277,186,1925]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Megaselia anniduedahlae sp. n. male (Figs 1-10). 1. Frons. 2. Postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 3, proboscis from below. 4, left face of hypopygium. 5. Right face of hypopygium. 6. Front leg. 7. segments 4 and 5 of front tarsus. 8. mid tibia. 9. Hind femur. 10. Wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617695/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Venter brownish gray, and with hairs on segments 3–6. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation box="[340,441,1779,1804]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[271,1255,201,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[225,1277,186,1925]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Megaselia anniduedahlae sp. n. male (Figs 1-10). 1. Frons. 2. Postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 3, proboscis from below. 4, left face of hypopygium. 5. Right face of hypopygium. 6. Front leg. 7. segments 4 and 5 of front tarsus. 8. mid tibia. 9. Hind femur. 10. Wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617695/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Figs 4–5</figureCitation>
. Legs brown. Fore tarsus with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–4 (
<figureCitation box="[1319,1423,1779,1804]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[271,1255,201,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[225,1277,186,1925]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Megaselia anniduedahlae sp. n. male (Figs 1-10). 1. Frons. 2. Postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 3, proboscis from below. 4, left face of hypopygium. 5. Right face of hypopygium. 6. Front leg. 7. segments 4 and 5 of front tarsus. 8. mid tibia. 9. Hind femur. 10. Wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617695/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Figs 6–7</figureCitation>
). Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.79 times its length (
<figureCitation box="[928,996,1815,1840]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[271,1255,201,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[225,1277,186,1925]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Megaselia anniduedahlae sp. n. male (Figs 1-10). 1. Frons. 2. Postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 3, proboscis from below. 4, left face of hypopygium. 5. Right face of hypopygium. 6. Front leg. 7. segments 4 and 5 of front tarsus. 8. mid tibia. 9. Hind femur. 10. Wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617695/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Hind femur as 
<figureCitation box="[1186,1255,1815,1840]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[271,1255,201,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[225,1277,186,1925]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Megaselia anniduedahlae sp. n. male (Figs 1-10). 1. Frons. 2. Postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 3, proboscis from below. 4, left face of hypopygium. 5. Right face of hypopygium. 6. Front leg. 7. segments 4 and 5 of front tarsus. 8. mid tibia. 9. Hind femur. 10. Wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617695/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
. Hind tibia with 15–16 differentiated posterodorsal hairs of which half are more robust and strongly differentiated, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[819,900,1887,1912]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[271,1255,201,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[225,1277,186,1925]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Megaselia anniduedahlae sp. n. male (Figs 1-10). 1. Frons. 2. Postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 3, proboscis from below. 4, left face of hypopygium. 5. Right face of hypopygium. 6. Front leg. 7. segments 4 and 5 of front tarsus. 8. mid tibia. 9. Hind femur. 10. Wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617695/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[915,1015,1887,1912]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.69" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="1.69">1.69 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.50. Costal ratios 3.15: 2.40: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[614,714,1924,1948]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="0.08">0.08 mm</quantity>
long. No hair at base of vein 3. With 2 unequal axillary bristles, the outer being 
<quantity box="[326,425,1960,1984]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="0.11">0.11 mm</quantity>
long. Sc raching R1. Haltere brown.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617695/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" startId="1.[151,264,1953,1976]" targetBox="[271,1255,201,1907]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1953,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,326,1953,1976]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">FIGURES 1–10.</emphasis>
