male (Figs 1-10). 1. Frons. 2. Postpedicels, palps and proboscis. 3, proboscis from below. 4, left face of hypopygium. 5. Right face of hypopygium. 6. Front leg. 7. segments 4 and 5 of front tarsus. 8. mid tibia. 9. Hind femur. 10. Wing.
